.TH "blk_poll" 9 "blk_poll" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blk_poll \- poll for IO completions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" blk_poll
.BI "(struct request_queue *q "  ","
.BI "blk_qc_t cookie "  ","
.BI "bool spin "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "q" 12
the queue
.IP "cookie" 12
cookie passed back at IO submission time
.IP "spin" 12
whether to spin for completions
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Poll for completions on the passed in queue. Returns number of
completed entries found. If \fIspin\fP is true, then blk_poll will continue
looping until at least one completion is found, unless the task is
otherwise marked running (or we need to reschedule).
